&lt;body&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin: 0cm; margin-bottom: .0001pt; text-align: justify; background: white;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;&quot;&gt;In these notes, written on a letter bearing the remnants of its red seal wax, Newton calculated, based on the Book of Daniel 7:25, that the end of time will arrive in the year &lt;b&gt;2060&lt;/b&gt;.&amp;#160; Newton&apos;s calculations relied on his belief that the starting point is the year 800, a time when Charlemagne founded the Holy Roman Empire and the Pope&apos;s supremacy commenced. Here, Newton believed, &amp;#160;began the period of the &quot;apostate&apos;s&quot; church deepest corruption which will end in the Apocalyptic events &lt;span style=&quot; color: black;&quot;&gt;such as plagues and fires, the terrible battle of Armageddon and eternal damnation of the wicked &lt;/span&gt;mentioned in the&amp;#160; &lt;span style=&quot; color: black;&quot;&gt;Book of Revelation.&amp;#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin: 0cm; margin-bottom: .0001pt; text-align: justify; background: white;&quot;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;DefaultStyle&quot;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin: 0cm; margin-bottom: .0001pt; text-align: justify; background: white;&quot;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;DefaultStyle&quot; style=&quot; margin-left: 54.2pt;&quot;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;DefaultStyle&quot; dir=&quot;RTL&quot; style=&quot; margin-right: 54.2pt; text-align: right; direction: rtl; unicode-bidi: embed;&quot;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
