&lt;/style&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: medium;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color: #ED1C24;&quot;&gt;The Torah used in the Synagogue is copied on specially prepared vellum or parchment by a scribe called Sofer Stam who specializes in copying sacred texts according to the ritual laws; it is sewn together in one piece and rolled up around two rollers with handles.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

&lt;!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd&quot;&gt;
