&lt;body&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot; margin-bottom: .0001pt; text-align: left; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed;&quot;&gt;Like many middle-class Jews in Prague, Kafka chose to continue his higher education at the German Charles Ferdinand University, where he at first studied chemistry and later law. It was during this period that he made the acquaintance of&amp;#160; Felix Weltsch, Oskar Baum, Franz Werfel, and Max Brod; Kafka, Weltsch and Brod would later call themselves &lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: 10.0pt; line-height: 115%; color: black; background: white;&quot;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color: black; background: white;&quot;&gt;Der enge Prager Kreis&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color: black; background: white;&quot;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color: black; background: white;&quot;&gt;(&quot;The Close Prague Circle&quot;).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

&lt;!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd&quot;&gt;&lt;html xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml&quot;&gt;
