&lt;p class=&quot;DefaultStyle&quot; align=&quot;left&quot; style=&quot; margin-left: 14.2pt; text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; background: white;&quot;&gt;With the arrival of the Jews who had been expelled from Spain in 1492, interest in Maimonides&apos; writings declined, and the Spanish Jewish tradition of Kabbalah and mysticism started to&amp;#160; flourish. &amp;#160;By the 17&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; century the library&#8217;s contents had been dispersed .&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;DefaultStyle&quot; align=&quot;left&quot; style=&quot; margin-left: 14.2pt; text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;DefaultStyle&quot; align=&quot;left&quot; style=&quot; margin-left: 14.2pt; text-align: left;&quot;&gt;photo:Latin translation of a Kabalah text, Gikatilla&apos;s &lt;i abp=&quot;1430&quot;&gt;Shaarei Ora&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
