&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;DefaultStyle&quot; align=&quot;left&quot; style=&quot; margin-left: 32.2pt; text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; background: white;&quot;&gt;The commentary was written in Judeo-Arabic , a dialect of Arabic that was spoken by Jews&amp;#160; living in the Arabic speaking world from the eighth century onwards, and is still spoken by some Jews today. &amp;#160;Although the language was Arabic, it was written in Hebrew letters. Many of the great medieval works of Jewish law and thought were written in Judeo-Arabic.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;DefaultStyle&quot; align=&quot;left&quot; style=&quot; margin-left: 36.0pt; text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;DefaultStyle&quot; align=&quot;left&quot; style=&quot; text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
