}
--&gt;
&lt;/style&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot; margin-bottom: .0001pt; text-align: left; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed;&quot;&gt;Kafka had many relationships with women. He had actually been betrothed to four of them, though none of these close relationships ever ended in marriage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot; margin-bottom: .0001pt; text-align: left; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed;&quot;&gt;During WWI&amp;#160; Kafka received a draft notice.&amp;#160; At first he was exempted by his employers; later, in 1917, when he attempted to enlist, Kafka was diagnosed with Tuberculosis, from which he suffered increasingly until his painful death in 1924.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

&lt;!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd&quot;&gt; 
&lt;html xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml&quot;&gt;
