margin-top: 0pt;  margin-bottom: 0pt;
}
--&gt;
&lt;/style&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;In this letter Benjamin mentions to Scholem his intention of staying in Ibiza for a while, a plan which will materialize somewhat later. &amp;#160;He also informs him of a new manuscript he will soon be sending. Benjamin notes that &quot;&lt;b&gt;this text is especially meant to adorn your archive&quot;, probably because it refers to Hebrew as well&lt;/b&gt;. The typescript which bears the title &lt;i&gt;&#220;ber die &lt;b&gt;Sprache&lt;/b&gt; &#252;berhaupt und &#252;ber die &lt;b&gt;Sprache&lt;/b&gt; des Menschen&lt;/i&gt;, &lt;i&gt;also hebr&#228;isch&lt;/i&gt; (&lt;i&gt;About language as such, and about the language of people, as well as about Hebrew&lt;/i&gt;) &lt;b&gt;was indeed sent and is found in the Walter Benjamin archives.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

&lt;!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd&quot;&gt; 
&lt;html xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml&quot;&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
